    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="615"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> and Prime
                        Minister <persName>Churchill</persName> to the Commander in Chief, Allied
                        Force Headquarters</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eisenhower</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-08">September 8,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From President and Prime Minister to General Eisenhower, Algiers.</p>
                <p>We agree with line you are taking as indicated in your 387<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d615fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> and are withholding all announcements
                    here and in London until we know what you have said and done.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d615fn2">Eisenhower broadcast his announcement of the armistice (see
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1267">p. 1267</ref>) at
                        6:30 p.m., Algiers time, September 8, 1943. See Garland and Smyth, p. 508. A
                        draft of this telegram, in Leahy’s handwriting, signed by Roosevelt and
                        initialed by Churchill, is in the Roosevelt Papers.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Churchill</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
